<br>
My tips:<br>
<br>
--/whisper task.  Keep it hotkeyed and use it often.  Good money, good experience and usually very easy.<br>
<br>
--As Dizoc said, the rewards for quests are significant and make the quests very worthwhile.  Pay attention to everything NPCs say as well.  There are clues to people that are offering quests given by NPCs that aren't offering quests but seem to talk a lot.<br>
<br>
--Explore, explore, explore...especially before you hit level 6.  Its easy and its very worthwhile.  If you don't bind and you die far away, just explore the other direction <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  I've seen all of Hibernia from one end of the main road to the other...all before level 6.<br>
<br>
--Melees...don't save up for the orange armor if your current armor is green or blue.  Buy the cheaper yellow stuff.  It REALLY makes a difference.  And buy better armor before you buy better weapons.<br>
<br>
--Group often.  Group with anyone.  I grouped for the first time the other night...Blademaster(me), Hero, and a Nightstalker.  We were getting experience at about 3 times the rate I was solo.  While I'm only level 6 and they were 8 and 9, we were killing reds with ease and with the quick regen rate, were right back to fighting very quickly without a healer.  Something I'm not used to coming from EQ.<br>
<br>
That's about it for now.  I'm still learnin. <p>-----------------------------------------<br>
